The Kwara State government is set to immortalise late Super Eagles legend, Rashidi Yekini. Yekini, who died on May 4 2012 at the age of 48 in the ancient city of Ibadan, Oyo State was renowned for his goalscoring prowess during his time with the Super Eagles. Yekini’s immortalisation was disclosed by the Kwara State governor, AbdulRahman Abdul- Razaq yesterday in Abuja. Governor AbdulRazaq announced that progress has been made in immortalising Yekini by naming the Kwara State Sports Complex Stadium in Ilorin after him. “We will send a bill to the House of Assembly to immortalise Rashidi Yekini by naming the Sports Complex Stadium in Ilorin after the approval,” he said. Yekini holds the record for the most goals scored in the nation- al team shirt with 37 goals in 58 international appearances. He scored Nigeria’s first-ever goal at the FIFA World Cup tournament in USA ‘94, and he was named the African Footballer of the Year in 1993.